We are working on an immediate update to give users the option to not share data.

content: Dual sim feature still not available/working on my huawei P8. Will try on my sony z3 dual for the tools.
replyContent: This is Android/Device limitation, not our limitation. Android does not currently explicitly support dual sim cell signal strengths. So only few phones that implement fully/correctly the telephony API can work correctly for 2SIM. Mostly MediaTek-powered devices (and not all of them). https://code.google.com/p/android/issues/detail?id=199699

content: Will it ever be possible to support dual sims?
replyContent: Thank you, we are working for dual sim support, but the results' reliability will be very device/api specific... This is because current official Android doesn't have explicit dual sim cell info and signal strength support. You may vote here: https://code.google.com/p/android/issues/detail?id=187127 , or create your own dual sim request to Android.
